      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09C\",\"process_rule\":\"1. From the input decision table, create a temporary table `J09C_temp` that contains only rows where the tour identifier starts with `J09C`.\\n\\n2. In `J09C_temp`, add a new column named `ENTSCHEIDUNG`.\\n\\n3. Classify meter reading type in `J09C_temp` by filling `ENTSCHEIDUNG` using these rules:\\n   - For each `HAUS`, count how many meters (`EQUNR`) it has.\\n   - If a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"KSA\\\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`; else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"EVU\\\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`.\\n   - Then override: for all rows where `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"EVU\\\"` (even if previously set to `\\\"KSA\\\"`).\\n\\n4. Join `J09C_temp` with the `EABLG` table using the `INSTALLATION` field as the join key to enrich each row with the corresponding EABLG data.\\n\\n5. Join the result with both `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` tables using `EQUNR` as the join key (i.e., `JOIN` with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` on `EQUNR`).\\n\\n6. For each joined record, compare the customer data coming from `SALES_MASTER` with the customer data coming from `NET_MASTER` to determine if the sales customer data is available (not empty).\\n\\n7. For each record, choose the customer data source according to this decision:\\n   - If the sales customer data from `SALES_MASTER` for the record is NOT empty:\\n     - Use the sales customer data table entries (from `SALES_MASTER`) as the customer fields in the final dataset for that record.\\n   - Else:\\n     - Use the net data customer table entries (from `NET_MASTER`) as the customer fields in the final dataset for that record.\\n\\n8. Export the final joined and classified dataset as a CSV file named `J09C` (e.g., `J09C.csv`). When exporting, include and name the columns exactly as:\\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n\\n9. Send an email to the EVU with the exported CSV attached:\\n   - Recipient email address: `meter.readings@evu.com`.\\n   - Attach the CSV file located at `&lt;path_to_exported_csv_file&gt;` (this path must point to the exported `J09C` CSV file).\\n\\n10. After the email is successfully sent, delete the temporary table `J09C_temp` used during processing.\"}",
            "id": "lc_0467098b-9601-4728-a7cf-8d9ef2b4cdb8"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "f75887c1-b805-4827-8ebd-d96492c668d4",
        "tool_call_id": "call_Ezs5rmRsQwl7Tlu4zO3ylBAK",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09C",
            "process_rule": "1. From the input decision table, create a temporary table `J09C_temp` that contains only rows where the tour identifier starts with `J09C`.\n\n2. In `J09C_temp`, add a new column named `ENTSCHEIDUNG`.\n\n3. Classify meter reading type in `J09C_temp` by filling `ENTSCHEIDUNG` using these rules:\n   - For each `HAUS`, count how many meters (`EQUNR`) it has.\n   - If a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"KSA\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`; else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"EVU\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`.\n   - Then override: for all rows where `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"EVU\"` (even if previously set to `\"KSA\"`).\n\n4. Join `J09C_temp` with the `EABLG` table using the `INSTALLATION` field as the join key to enrich each row with the corresponding EABLG data.\n\n5. Join the result with both `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` tables using `EQUNR` as the join key (i.e., `JOIN` with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` on `EQUNR`).\n\n6. For each joined record, compare the customer data coming from `SALES_MASTER` with the customer data coming from `NET_MASTER` to determine if the sales customer data is available (not empty).\n\n7. For each record, choose the customer data source according to this decision:\n   - If the sales customer data from `SALES_MASTER` for the record is NOT empty:\n     - Use the sales customer data table entries (from `SALES_MASTER`) as the customer fields in the final dataset for that record.\n   - Else:\n     - Use the net data customer table entries (from `NET_MASTER`) as the customer fields in the final dataset for that record.\n\n8. Export the final joined and classified dataset as a CSV file named `J09C` (e.g., `J09C.csv`). When exporting, include and name the columns exactly as:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n\n9. Send an email to the EVU with the exported CSV attached:\n   - Recipient email address: `meter.readings@evu.com`.\n   - Attach the CSV file located at `&lt;path_to_exported_csv_file&gt;` (this path must point to the exported `J09C` CSV file).\n\n10. After the email is successfully sent, delete the temporary table `J09C_temp` used during processing."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
